{"title_page": "Thelma (2017 film)", "text_new": "{{distinguish|text= the 1922 film of the same name by [[Thomas Dixon Jr.]]}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Thelma\n| image          = Thelma (2017 film).jpg\n| alt            = <!-- Alt text for the image for visually impaired reader. See [[WP:ALT]]. -->\n| caption        = United States theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Joachim Trier]]\n| producer       = [[Thomas Robsahm]]\n| screenplay     = {{plainlist|\n* Joachim Trier\n* [[Eskil Vogt]]}}\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* [[Eili Harboe]] \n* Kaya Wilkins\n* Henrik Rafaelsen\n* Ellen Dorrit Petersen\n}}Amil Ramkisson\n| music          = Ola Fl\u00f8ttum\n| cinematography = Jakob Ihre\n| editing        = Olivier Bugge Coutt\u00e9\n| production companies = {{plainlist|\n* Motlys\n* [[Film i V\u00e4st|Film V\u00e4st]]\n* Snowglobe Film\n* Filmpool Nord\n* [[B-Reel]]\n* Le Pacte\n}}\n| distributor    = [[SF Studios]] {{small|([[Scandinavia]])}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2017|8|20|[[Norwegian International Film Festival]]|2017|9|15|Norway|2017|11|3|United Kingdom|2017|11|10|United States|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 116 minutes\n| country        = {{plainlist|\n* Norway\n* Sweden\n* Denmark\n* France\n}}\n| language       = Norwegian\n| budget         = $5.8 million<ref name=budget />\n| gross          = $1.5 million<ref name=BOM>{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=thelma.htm|website=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[Amazon (company)|Amazon]]|date=2017|accessdate=23 January 2019}} (Box office total based on manual addition of BOM grosses.)</ref><ref name=Numbers>{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=https://www.the-numbers.com/movie/Thelma-(Norway)#tab=summary|website=[[The Numbers (website)|The Numbers]]|publisher=Nash Information Services|date=2017|accessdate=23 January 2019}} (Box office total underrepresented.)</ref> <!-- Both BOM and Numbers have insufficient reportage. BOM shows N/A for Foreign. Numbers has no total for Norway. \"|date=\" found in Foreign (BOM) / International (Numbers) -->\n}}\n'''''Thelma''''' is a 2017 [[Norway|Norwegian]] [[supernatural]] [[Thriller film|thriller]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama film]] directed by [[Joachim Trier]]. The screenplay was written by Trier and [[Eskil Vogt]]. The film stars [[Eili Harboe]], Kaya Wilkins, Henrik Rafaelsen, and Ellen Dorrit Petersen. ''Thelma'' tells the story of a sheltered young woman who discovers she has an inexplicable power that materializes when she feels desire for a female student at her university.\n\nThe film premiered at the [[Norwegian International Film Festival]] on 20 August 2017.<ref name=filmfestivalen>{{cite web|last1=Pressemeldinger (Press Release)|title=Thelma \u00e5pner Den norske filmfestivalen|url=https://filmfestivalen.no/thelma-apner-norske-filmfestivalen/|website=[[Norwegian International Film Festival|Den Norske Filmfestivalen i Haugesund]]|date=11 July 2017 |accessdate=24 June 2018|language=Norwegian|quote=Thelma Opens the Norwegian Film Festival.}}</ref><ref name=JensenNordic>{{cite web|last1=Jensen|first1=Jorn Rossing|title=Joachim Trier\u2019s \u2018Thelma\u2019 Opens Nordic Encounter in Haugesund|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/festivals/joachim-triers-thelma-opens-nordic-encounter-haugesund-1202499711/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=19 July 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref> ''Thelma'' held its international premiere at the [[2017 Toronto International Film Festival|Toronto International Film Festival]] as a Special Presentation on 9 September 2017.<ref name=\"TIFF\">{{cite web|title=The Toronto International Film Festival unveils first slate of films for 2017|url=https://www.tiff.net/the-review/the-toronto-international-film-festival-unveils-first-slate-of-films-for/|publisher=[[Toronto International Film Festival]]|date=25 July 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=DeadlineTIFF>{{cite web|last1=Fleming Jr.|first1=Mike|title=Toronto Film Festival 2017 Unveils Strong Slate|url=https://deadline.com/2017/07/toronto-film-festival-2017-margot-robbie-gary-oldman-jake-gyllenhaal-emma-stone-christian-bale-1202135285/|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=25 July 2017|accessdate=25 July 2017}}</ref><ref name=Grierson>{{cite web|last1=Grierson|first1=Tim|title='Thelma': Toronto Review|url=https://www.screendaily.com/reviews/thelma-toronto-review/5121716.article|website=[[Screen Daily]]|date=9 September 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref> It premiered in the United States at [[Fantastic Fest]] on 21 September 2017,<ref name=Fantastic>{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=http://fantasticfest.com/films/thelma/|website=[[Fantastic Fest]]|date=2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=Collis>{{cite web|last1=Collis|first1=Clark|title=A student gains supernatural abilities in Thelma trailer|url=http://ew.com/movies/2017/09/06/thelma-trailer-tiff-toronto-film-festival/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=6 September 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=Galgana>{{cite web|last1=Galgana|first1=Michele|title=Fantastic Fest 2017 Review: THELMA Thrills With Lust and Existentialism|url=http://screenanarchy.com/2017/09/fantastic-fest-2017-review-thelma-thrills.html|website=[[Screen Anarchy]]|date=22 September 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref> and screened at the [[New York Film Festival]] as a Main Slate selection on 6 October 2017.<ref name=NYFF>{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=https://www.filmlinc.org/nyff2017/films/thelma/|website=[[New York Film Festival]]|date=2017|accessdate=29 September 2018}}</ref><ref name=Criterion>{{cite web|last1=Hudson|first1=David|title=NYFF 2017: Joachim Trier\u2019s Thelma|url=https://www.criterion.com/current/posts/5018-nyff-2017-joachim-trier-s-thelma|website=The Daily|publisher=[[The Criterion Collection]]|date=7 October 2017|accessdate=29 September 2018}}</ref> It premiered in the United Kingdom at the [[BFI London Film Festival]] as a Cult Gala presentation on 14 October 2017.<ref name=BFIFestival>{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=https://whatson.bfi.org.uk/lff/Online/default.asp?BOparam::WScontent::loadArticle::permalink=thelma&BOparam::WScontent::loadArticle::context_id=|website=[[BFI London Film Festival]]|publisher=[[British Film Institute]]|date=2017|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Calendar|url=http://www.emagcloud.com/bfi/LFF_Calendar_Page_Turner/pubData/source/LFF%20Calendar%20Page%20Turner.pdf|work=[[BFI London Film Festival|BFI London Film Festival 2017]]|publisher=[[British Film Institute]]|date=2017|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Norwegian film at London Film Festival|url=http://norwegianarts.org.uk/event/norwegian-film-at-london-film-festival/|website=Norwegian Arts|publisher=[[Embassy of Norway, London|Royal Norwegian Embassy]]|date=4 October 2017|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref> ''Thelma'' was [[Theatrical release|released]] in theatres in Norway on 15 September 2017.\n\n''Thelma'' was selected as the Norwegian entry for the [[Academy Awards|Oscar]] as [[Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]] at the [[90th Academy Awards]],<ref name=\"NRK\">{{cite web|last1=Alnes|first1= Espen|url=https://www.nrk.no/kultur/_thelma_-blir-den-norske-oscar-kandidaten-1.13673658|title=\"Thelma\" blir den norske Oscar-kandidaten|website=[[NRK]]|date=5 September 2017|accessdate=6 September 2017|language=Norwegian|quote=\"Thelma\" the Norwegian Oscar candidate.}}</ref><ref name=Keslassy>{{cite web|last1=Keslassy|first1=Elsa|title=Joachim Trier\u2019s \u2018Thelma\u2019 Chosen by Norway for Foreign-Language Oscar|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/global/joachim-triers-thema-chosen-by-norway-to-run-for-foreign-language-oscar-nomination-1202548687/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=6 September 2017|accessdate=6 September 2017}}</ref><ref name=CineuropaOscars>{{cite web|last1=Jensen|first1=Jorn Rossing|title=Thelma and her supernatural powers put forward for the Oscars|url=http://cineuropa.org/en/newsdetail/334062/|website=Cineuropa|date=6 September 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref> but did not receive the [[List of submissions to the 90th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film|nomination]].<ref name=Oscars92>{{cite web|last1=Kilday|first1=Gregg|title=Oscars: 92 Films Submitted in Foreign-Language Category|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-92-films-submitted-foreign-language-film-academy-award-1046070|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=5 October 2017|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=shortlist>{{cite web|last1=Kilday|first1=Gregg|title=Oscars: Academy Unveils Foreign-Language Film Shortlist|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/oscars-academy-unveils-foreign-language-film-shortlist-1068109|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=14 December 2017|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n<!--[[WP:FILMPLOT]]: \"Plot summaries for feature films should be between 400 and 700 words....all of the film's important events should be outlined without censoring details considered spoilers.\" Describe plot without POV speculations.-->\n\nThelma is a lonely and repressed young woman from an ultra-religious Christian family who has lived a sheltered life under the protection of her father, Trond, and disabled mother, Unni. She struggles to make friends and soon after moving to [[Oslo]] to attend university begins to experience unexplained [[epileptic seizure]]s. When she meets another student, Anja, she discovers that her feelings for Anja trigger uncontrollable [[Psychokinesis|psychokinetic]] powers.\n\nWhile undergoing a brain tomography test to find the cause of her seizures, she begins to think about Anja and as she focuses on her, Thelma's power is set in motion and she unconsciously and unwittingly makes Anja vanish into empty space. Distraught and confused by Anja's sudden disappearance, Thelma returns home and soon remembers that when she was a little girl she had a baby brother. Once, when feeling neglected and jealous of the attention given to her younger sibling, and wishing him to be quiet and gone, she involuntarily caused him to [[Teleportation|teleport]] from his crib and reappear underneath the sofa. In a final tragic incident, she caused him to disappear from his bath, and he was found trapped below the ice of a frozen lake by her father. Traumatized, Thelma's mother tried to commit suicide by jumping off a bridge; but instead the failed attempt left her disabled. Thelma had forgotten these events. Realising her utter distress, her parents tell her the truth, which is that she is somehow able to manifest whatever she deeply wants; and that she inherited the same inexplicable ability from her grandmother, who blamed herself for the disappearance of Thelma's grandfather, and was kept sedated in a psychiatric nursing home by Trond. Thelma perceives that her parents had a similar fate in mind for her.\n\nEarlier, while visiting Anja, Thelma recalled how her father once held her hand over a lit candle until it almost burned so that she could feel what Hell's eternal fire was like. She causes the death of her father by telekinetically making him [[Spontaneous human combustion|self-combust]] whilst out boating on the unfrozen lake. Thelma realizes that her power can also restore life when she revives a small dead bird. She begins to understand that her supernatural ability is also a gift and uses it to heal her mother, making her able to walk again. Along with the realization that she can summon her power, Thelma is able to finally control it, and brings Anja back to existence. She returns to college, now with Anja as her girlfriend in a guilt-free relationship.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Eili Harboe]] as Thelma\n**Grethe Elterv\u00e5g as young Thelma\n* Kaya Wilkins as Anja\n* Henrik Rafaelsen as Trond\n* Ellen Dorrit Petersen as Unni\n\n==Production==\n\n''Thelma'' was produced by [[Thomas Robsahm]] of Norwegian production company Motlys, and co-produced by [[Film i V\u00e4st|Film V\u00e4st]], Filmpool Nord and [[B-Reel]] (Sweden), Snowglobe Film (Denmark), and Le Pacte (France); with financial support provided by the [[Norwegian Film Institute]], [[Swedish Film Institute]], [[Danish Film Institute]], Copenhagen Film Fund, Nordic Film & TV Fund, [[Eurimages]], and [[MEDIA Programme]].<ref name=LePacte>{{cite web|last1=Mitchell|first1=Wendy|title=Le Pacte joins Joachim Trier\u2019s 'Thelma'|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/le-pacte-joins-joachim-triers-thelma/5109608.article|website=[[Screen Daily]]|date=21 September 2016|accessdate=7 January 2017}}</ref> The final production [[Film budgeting|budget]]{{efn|The first reported budget was 39 million [[Norwegian krone|NOK]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Joachim Triers Thelma har et budsjett p\u00e5 39 millioner kroner|url=http://montages.no/nyheter/joachim-triers-thelma-har-et-budsjett-pa-39-millioner-kroner/|website=Montages|date=2 June 2016|accessdate=22 September 2018|language=Norwegian|quote=(Joachim Trier's Thelma Has A Budget Of 39 Million Kroner)}}</ref>}} was [[Euro|\u20ac]]5,009,000 (47 million [[Norwegian krone|NOK]], 5.8 million [[United States dollar|USD]]).<ref name=budget>{{cite web|last1=|first1=|title=Facts & Figures 2017|url=https://www.dfi.dk/files/docs/2018-02/ff2017pdf.pdf|publisher=[[Danish Film Institute]]|page=8|date=February 2018|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref> <!-- Differences in the total have been published by various sources. DFI source was published in 2018. -->\n\n[[Principal photography]] began on 20 September 2016 and lasted 44 days.<ref name=LePacte /> [[Filming location|Locations]] included [[Oslo]] in Norway, and [[V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland County|V\u00e4stra G\u00f6taland]], [[Gothenburg]], [[Trollh\u00e4ttan]] and [[Kiruna]] in [[Sweden]].<ref name=LePacte /><ref name=shooting>{{cite web|last1=Jensen|first1=Jorn Rossing|title=Joachim Trier shooting Thelma|url=http://cineuropa.org/en/newsdetail/319045/|website=Cineuropa|date=26 October 2016|accessdate=7 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe [[film poster]] was released in August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Se den lekre kinoplakaten til Joachim Triers Thelma |url=http://montages.no/nyheter/se-den-lekre-kinoplakaten-til-joachim-triers-thelma/|website=Montages |accessdate=22 September 2018|date=18 August 2017|language=Norwegian |quote=(See the Gorgeous Movie Poster for Joachim Trier's Thelma)}}</ref> The key art for the U.S. was released in September 2017 in advance of the American premiere;<ref>{{cite web|last1=Foss|first1=Truls|title=Amerikansk trailer og plakat til Joachim Triers Thelma|url=http://montages.no/nyheter/amerikansk-trailer-og-plakat-til-joachim-triers-thelma/|website=Montages|date=7 September 2017|accessdate=22 September 2018|language=Norwegian |quote=(American Trailer and Poster for Joachim Trier's Thelma)}}</ref><ref name=Playlist /> followed by the UK in October.<ref>{{cite web|title=Thunderbird Releasing unveils new trailer & quad poster for 'Thelma'|url=https://www.theartsshelf.com/2017/10/20/thunderbird-releasing-unveils-new-trailer-quad-poster-for-thelma/|website=The Arts Shelf|date=20 October 2017|accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Donnis|first1=Jon|title=Thelma - UK poster and trailer|url=http://www.beentothemovies.com/2017/10/thelma-uk-poster-and-trailer.html|website=BeenToTheMovies|date=20 October 2017|accessdate=22 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\n===Theatrical===\n''Thelma'' was released [[Art release|theatrically]] in Norway on 15 September 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=Her er den norske filmh\u00f8sten|url=https://www.nfi.no/aktuelt/2017/her-er-den-norske-filmhosten|website=[[Norwegian Film Institute|Norsk filminstitutt]]|date=2017|accessdate=25 June 2018|language=Norwegian |quote=Here are autumn Norwegian films.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Thelma [@thelmafilmen]|title=Endelig premiere i dag!|url=https://www.facebook.com/thelmafilmen/photos/a.404320196620592.1073741828.392525504466728/464932877225990/?type=3&theater|publisher=[[Facebook]]|date=15 September 2017|accessdate=25 June 2018|language=Norwegian |quote=Finally premiere today!}}</ref> It was released in the United Kingdom on 3 November 2017,<ref>{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=https://www.launchingfilms.com/release-schedule?filmSearch=Thelma|website=Launching Films|publisher=Film Distributors' Association|date=2017|accessdate=24 June 2018 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Thunderbird Releasing [@TBirdReleasing]|title=Featuring an \"outstanding performance\" from Eili Harboe (@guardianfilm) telekinetic thriller #Thelma is out tomorrow|url=https://twitter.com/TBirdReleasing/status/926133810244345858|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=2 November 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref> followed by the United States on 10 November 2017.<ref name=Playlist>{{cite web|last1=Davis|first1=Edward|title='Thelma' Exclusive: New Poster For Joachim Trier's Supernatural Drama|url=https://theplaylist.net/thelma-exclusive-poster-20170905/|website=The Playlist|date=5 September 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Thelma Film US [@ThelmaFilmUS]|title=Sometimes the most terrifying discovery is who you really are\u2014Discover Thelma on November 10.|url=https://twitter.com/ThelmaFilmUS/status/906278156314619904|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=8 September 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn April 2017, [[The Orchard (company)|The Orchard]] acquired the North American distribution rights to the film.<ref name=Orchard>{{cite web|last1=Press Release|title=The Orchard Lands Joachim Trier\u2019s Supernatural Thriller \"Thelma\"|url=http://www.theorchard.com/press/orchard-lands-joachim-triers-supernatural-thriller-thelma/|website=[[The Orchard (company)|The Orchard]]|date=20 April 2017|accessdate=29 June 2018 }}</ref><ref name=OrchardVariety>{{cite web|last1=Lang|first1=Brent|last2=Keslassy|first2=Elsa |title=The Orchard Nabs Joachim Trier\u2019s Supernatural Thriller \u2018Thelma\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE)|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/markets-festivals/the-orchard-nabs-joachim-triers-thelma-exclusive-1202391211/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=20 April 2017|accessdate=20 April 2017}}</ref> Distribution rights to the United Kingdom were acquired by [[Thunderbird Releasing]] in August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Grater|first1=Tom|title=Joachim Trier's 'Thelma' gets UK deal (exclusive)|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/joachim-triers-thelma-gets-uk-deal-exclusive/5121858.article|website=[[Screen Daily]]|date=31 August 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Home media===\nThe [[DVD]] for [[DVD region code#Region codes and countries|Region 2]] and [[Blu-ray]] for [[Blu-ray#Region codes|Region B]] was released by [[SF Studios]] in [[Scandinavia]] on 4 December 2017.<ref name=\"Bergedvd\">{{cite web|last1=Berge|first1=John|title=H\u00f8stutgivelser 2017 fra SF Studios p\u00e5 Blu-ray og DVD|url=http://www.videomagasinet.no/artikkel/hostutgivelser-2017-fra-sf-studios-pa-video/|website=VIDEOMAGASINET|publisher=JB Forlag|date=19 October 2017|accessdate=25 June 2018|language=Norwegian |quote=Fall Releases 2017 from SF Studios on Blu-ray and DVD}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thelma Blu-ray|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Thelma-Blu-ray/192431/|website=Blu-ray.com|date=2017|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref> They were released in the UK by Thunderbird Releasing on 26 February 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Supernatural Thriller THELMA Released|url=https://horrorisland.uk/supernatural-thriller-thelma-released/|website=Horror Island UK|date=26 February 2018|accessdate=1 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thelma Blu-ray (UK)|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/movies/Thelma-Blu-ray/192407/|website=Blu-ray.com|date=2018|accessdate=30 June 2018}}</ref> In [[DVD region code#Region codes and countries|Region 1]] the DVD was released by The Orchard through Passion River Films on 3 April 2018.<ref name=\"Passion\">{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=http://www.passionriver.com/thelma.html|website=Passion River Films|date=2018|accessdate=30 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Thelma DVD|url=http://www.blu-ray.com/dvd/Thelma-DVD/155473/|website=Blu-ray.com|date=2018|accessdate=30 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nOn [[review aggregator]]  [[Rotten Tomatoes]], ''Thelma'' holds an approval rating of 92% based on {{nowrap|143 reviews}}, with an [[weighted average|average]] rating of 7.29/10. The website's critical consensus reads, \"''Thelma'' plays with genre tropes in unexpected ways, delivering a thoughtfully twisty supernatural thriller with a lingering impact.\"<ref name=\"RT\">{{cite web|title=Thelma|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/thelma_2017/|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|publisher=[[Fandango Media]]|date=2017|accessdate=18 July 2019}}</ref> On [[Metacritic]], the film received a score of 74 out of 100, based on 31 leading critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref>{{cite web |title=Thelma|url=http://www.metacritic.com/movie/thelma|website=[[Metacritic]]|publisher=[[CBS Interactive]]|date=2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> In ''[[IndieWire]]'''s annual critics poll of best films and performances, ''Thelma'' was selected a \"Critics Pick\" for Best Foreign Language Film.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kohn|first1=Eric|title=2017 Critics Poll: The Best Films and Performances According to Over 200 Critics|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/12/best-movies-2017-critics-films-performances-get-out-phantom-thread-lady-bird-1201909032/3/|website=[[IndieWire]]|date=19 December 2017|accessdate=25 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Manohla Dargis]] wrote in ''[[The New York Times]]'' that ''Thelma'' is \"a romance, a psychological thriller, a liberation story and a whodunit (and why) ... and most satisfyingly, it plays with the female Gothic ... in which women are at once the victims and agents of change\", praising Joachim Trier with having \"a great talent for making loneliness visceral and visible, for showing how pain can make the world disappear.\"<ref name=Dargis>{{cite web|last1=Dargis|first1= Manohla|title=Review: In \u2018Thelma,\u2019 a Woman in Love Can Burn Down the World|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/09/movies/review-in-thelma-a-woman-in-love-can-burn-down-the-world.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=9 November 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> In the ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'', [[Justin Chang]] said the film was a \"muted and moody supernatural chiller\" that is \"thoughtful and beautifully composed\" with sequences \"that tap into a vividly primal sense of terror.\"<ref name=Chang>{{cite web|last1= Chang|first1=Justin|title=Joachim Trier's supernatural thriller \u2018Thelma\u2019 takes an unsettling look at religion and sexuality|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/movies/la-et-mn-thelma-review-20171122-story.html|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=22 November 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n[[Peter Bradshaw]] of ''[[The Guardian]]'' described ''Thelma'' as \"an uncanny accumulation of mood, an ecstasy of disquiet\" and the performance by Eili Harboe as \"outstandingly good\".<ref name=Bradshaw>{{cite web|last1=Bradshaw|first1=Peter|title=Thelma review \u2013 telekinetic lesbian drama is scary, sexy and cool|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/nov/02/thelma-review-joachim-trier-telekenetic-lesbian-psychological-drama|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2 November 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> ''[[AfterEllen]]'' praised the performance by Harboe as \"exhilarating, and incredibly moving\", and said that \"In a sea of lesbian films that are often repetitive, ''Thelma'' explores analytical territory that none other has before.\"<ref name=Pitts>{{cite web|last1=Pitts|first1=Ciara|title=Sapphic Cinema: \u2018Thelma\u2019 is a Liberating Lesbian Love Story|url=http://www.afterellen.com/movies/550795-thelma-liberating-lesbian-love-story|website=[[AfterEllen]]|date=18 December 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> David Friend of ''[[The Canadian Press]]'' said the film carries \"an ominous and sinister tone that evokes the best traits of classics like 'Carrie' and 'Let the Right One In.'\"<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Friend|first1=David||url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/entertainment/five-to-watch-standout-tiff-films-that-flew-under-the-radar-1.3592606|title=Five to watch: Standout TIFF films that flew under the radar|website=[[CTV News]]|date=16 September 2017|accessdate=7 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[Bilge Ebiri]] of ''[[The Village Voice]]'' described the film's story as moving \"away from the monstrous, toward compassion and understanding ... prob[ing] the profound underlying sadness beneath tales of possession\" and \"makes vivid the protagonist\u2019s loneliness and despair.\"<ref name=Ebiri>{{cite web|last1=Ebiri|first1=Bilge|title=\"Thelma\" Skips the Jump Scares, But It\u2019s Still Deeply Disturbing|url=https://www.villagevoice.com/2017/11/08/thelma-skips-the-jump-scares-but-its-still-deeply-disturbing/|work=[[The Village Voice]]|date=8 November 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> David Ehrlich wrote in ''[[IndieWire]]'' that ''Thelma'' was a \"an ominous, unnerving, and strangely powerful thriller about the most devious of human desires\" and \"consistently keyed in to the persuasive power of the female body.\"<ref name=Ehrlich>{{cite web|last1= Erhlich|first1=David |title=\u2018Thelma\u2019 Review: Ingmar Bergman Meets Stephen King in Joachim Trier\u2019s Beguiling Lesbian Horror Movie|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/09/thelma-review-joachim-trier-tiff-2017-1201873811/|website=[[IndieWire]]|date=9 September 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Verge]]'' said ''Thelma'' was a \"quietly beautiful film\" and \"a thriller that\u2019s scary, sad, and ultimately triumphant\", with cinematography that is \"visually ... striking throughout\".<ref name=Bishop>{{cite web|last1=Bishop|first1=Bryan|title=Thelma is a superhero horror movie about the terror of growing up|url=https://www.theverge.com/2017/11/10/16633718/thelma-movie-review-joachim-trier-superhero-horror|website=[[The Verge]]|date=10 November 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' said it contained \"intelligent, measured tone and elegant visual style\" and \"while the more enigmatic supernatural elements at times veer close to formulaic Hollywood horror tropes, the movie maintains a compelling seriousness, particularly in its consideration of the conflict between sexuality and repression.\"<ref name=Rooney>{{cite web|last1=Rooney|first1=David|title='Thelma': Film Review \u2013 TIFF 2017|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/thelma-tiff-1033327|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=9 September 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> THR also selected ''Thelma'' as one of the best [[LGBT]] films of 2017.<ref>{{cite web|author=THR Staff|title=The Year in Queer: Hollywood Reporter Critics Pick the Best LGBT Films of 2017|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/year-queer-thr-critics-pick-best-lgbt-films-2017-1068540/item/wound-best-lgbt-films-2017-1068577|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=18 December 2017|accessdate=29 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' described the film as \"an unnervingly effective slow-burn, and those with the patience for Trier\u2019s patient accumulation of detail will find it pays off in unexpected ways.\"<ref name=Barker>{{cite web|last1=Barker|first1=Andrew|title=Film Review: \u2018Thelma\u2019|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/reviews/toronto-film-review-thelma-1202560589/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=15 September 2017|accessdate=23 June 2018}}</ref> Margaret Barton-Fumo from ''[[Film Comment]]'' summarized ''Thelma'' as \"a romantic film that pays close attention to physical detail\", and \"Surprisingly tender, [it] proves itself a modern take on the supernatural film.\"<ref>{{cite web|last1=Barton-Fumo|first1=Margaret|title=Short Take: Thelma|url=https://www.filmcomment.com/article/review-thelma-joachim-trier/|work=[[Film Comment]]|publisher=[[Film Society of Lincoln Center]]|date=November\u2013December 2017|accessdate=29 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n{{expand section|date=June 2018}}\n\n===Accolades===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:99%;\"\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Award\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Category\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Recipient and nominee\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Result\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#b0c4de;\"| Ref\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=1| [[Norwegian International Film Festival]]\n| rowspan=1| <center>24 August 2017</center>\n| Norwegian Critics Prize\n| ''Thelma''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=VarietyNCP>{{cite web|last1=Jensen|first1=Jorn Rossing|last2=Pham|first2=Annika|title=Haugesund: Joachim Trier\u2019s \u2018Thelma\u2019 Takes Norwegian Critics\u2019 Prize|url=https://variety.com/2017/film/news/haugesund-joachim-trier-thelma-norwegian-critics-prize-1202538210/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=24 August 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref><ref name=CineuropaNCP>{{cite web|last1=Jensen|first1=Jorn Rossing|title=Thelma wins over Norwegian critics in Haugesund|url=http://cineuropa.org/en/newsdetail/333531/|website=Cineuropa|date=25 August 2017|accessdate=24 June 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=1| [[L\u00fcbeck Nordic Film Days]]\n| rowspan=1| <center>5 November 2017</center>\n| Baltic Jury Award\n| ''Thelma''\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kalajdzic|first1=Pedja|title=Norske filmer vant priser i Tyskland|url=https://www.nrk.no/kultur/norske-filmer-vant-priser-i-tyskland-1.13765137|website=[[Norwegian Broadcasting Corporation|NRK]]|date=5 November 2017|accessdate=21 September 2018|language=Norwegian|quote=(Norwegian Films Won Awards in Germany)}}</ref>\n|-\n! sc